properties.headline: Australia Day in Sydney - Tuesday 26 January - CIRCULAR QUAY George Street, Hickson Road
properties.publicTransport: Some transport services around Circular Quay will be affected due to exclusion zones on the harbour and road closures. Visit transportnsw.info for details.

arrangementAttachments.displayName: Australia Day 2021 - Road closures & Clearways map
arrangementAttachments.linkName: Australia Day 2021 - Road closures & Clearways map

properties.otherAdvice:
Roads around Circular Quay and The Rocks will close in the morning and evening for Australia Day events in the city and around the harbour.

Circular Quay will be closed to the general public from 5pm. Access to the Circular Quay foreshore area after 5pm will only be permitted for those with a booking at a restaurant or venue, or a ticket for the Australia Day Live! Concert at the Sydney Opera House forecourt. Visit australiaday.com.au for details.

Key road closure timings:

  • From 4am to midnight: roads in Circular Quay and The Rocks including sections of Alfred St, Argyle St, Circular Quay West, Essex St and George St will close.
  • From 7am to midnight: Hickson Rd from George St to Pottinger St in The Rocks will close.
  • From 7am to 10am: Hickson Rd from Napoleon St to Towns Place and Towns Place from Dalgety Rd to Hickson Rd will close (for GIO Oz Day 10K wheelchair race).
  • From 7am to 11am: Hickson Rd from Towns Place to Pottinger St will close (for GIO Oz Day 10K wheelchair race).
  • From 7.30pm to 10.30pm: the Cahill Expressway lanes 7 and 8 southbound and lane 4 on the Harbour Bridge will close as well as both directions of the Cahill Expressway Circular Quay Overpass. Roads in Circular Quay north of Bridge St will also close including sections of Albert St, Alfred St, Essex St, George St, Loftus St, Phillip St and Young St will close.

The speed limit on the Harbour Bridge will be reduced to 40km/h from 8pm to 9.30pm.

The Cahill Expressway overpass walkway will be closed from 5pm to 9:30pm. The Sydney Harbour Bridge Walkway and Cycleway will remain open.

Special event clearways will be in effect on various roads in Circular Quay and The Rocks from 3am until midnight with additional clearways in place throughout the city on various roads between Circular Quay and Martin Place from 5pm until 10.30pm.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones, and apply even to local residents and businesses with parking permits and RMS Mobility Scheme permit holders. Check signs carefully on the day and the night before, as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed call 132 701 to find its new location.

properties.headline: Australia Day at Dee Why - Tuesday 26 January - DEE WHY The Strand between Dee Why Parade AND Oaks Avenue
properties.publicTransport: Buses will be diverting around The Strand. Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
Road closures and special event clearways will be in place to accommodate various events in Dee Why on Australia Day. 

Road closures will be in place from 12pm midday Monday 25 January until 6am Wednesday 27 January on The Strand between Dee Why Pde and Oaks Ave and on Howard Ave between Clyde Ave and The Strand.

Resident access to Howard Ave will be maintained via Clyde Rd throughout the closure period.

Special event clearways will also be in effect from 12pm midday on Monday to 6am on Wednesday along The Strand between Dee Why Pde and Oaks Ave.

 Clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.
